# cron.example — DOCUMENTED FALLBACK ONLY, never installed automatically.
#
# Use cron ONLY on hosts without systemd, and NEVER together with the
# systemd timers for the same command (duplicate scheduling contract,
# deploy/README-deploy.md §4). Cron runs in the HOST timezone: set the host
# to Africa/Cairo (timedatectl set-timezone Africa/Cairo) or adjust the
# hour. Cron has no Persistent= catch-up: a run missed while the host was
# down is skipped (the tick model catches up by itself within 24h).
#
# Install as /etc/cron.d/seo-audit-runner (mode 0644, owner root:root).
# Format: m h dom mon dow user command

# EITHER: classic daily full audit at 03:00 host time + hourly retry
0 3 * * *   seo-runner  /usr/local/bin/seo-audit-runner run --all >> /var/log/seo-audit-runner/cron.log 2>&1
0 * * * *   seo-runner  /usr/local/bin/seo-audit-runner retry-notifications >> /var/log/seo-audit-runner/cron.log 2>&1

# OR: scheduler tick every 5 minutes (runner-managed schedules; comment the
# daily line above if schedules cover the full audit)
#*/5 * * * * seo-runner  /usr/local/bin/seo-audit-runner worker --once >> /var/log/seo-audit-runner/cron.log 2>&1
